The operating cash flow (OCF) refers to the difference between the income and the outflow of cash. In this case, we will use the EBIT as the income and we will add in the depreciation since this is not considered as noncash which means it does not affect the cash flow. This will then give us this formula for the OCF:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{OCF}&=\text{EBIT}+\text{Depreciation}-\text{Tax}
\end{aligned}$$
